-- GaussianInteger/euclidean.math
--
-- ℤ[i] is a Euclidean domain under the norm. Division is nearest-integer:
-- to divide a by b ≠ 0, balanced-divide the coordinates of a·conj(b) by
-- D = N(b) to get a quotient q, and set r = a − b·q; then N(r) ≤ N(b)/2 <
-- N(b). The three arithmetic facts below isolate the pure ℤ / ℕ content of
-- that bound; the main theorem assembles them with the coordinate algebra.

module GaussianInteger.euclidean

